Text.SourceString: You’re <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=smile>I heard about you. I heard you’re looking for some fresh air away from the city.
Text.LocalizedString: You’re <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=smile>I heard about you. I heard you’re looking for some fresh air away from the city.

Text.SourceString: Well, I think you came to the right place.//I hope you find it here.//<portrait=daydreaming>Fresh air, peace of mind, whatever it might be.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I think you came to the right place.//I hope you find it here.//<portrait=daydreaming>Fresh air, peace of mind, whatever it might be.

Text.SourceString: I can tell ya one thing, <PlayerName>$player</>, rancher to rancher.//You need to talk to your animals to connect with them.
Text.LocalizedString: I can tell ya one thing, <PlayerName>$player</>, rancher to rancher.//You need to talk to your animals to connect with them.

Text.SourceString: Animals ain't much different from us folks.//<portrait=smile>That's somethin' my old man taught me.
Text.LocalizedString: Animals ain't much different from us folks.//<portrait=smile>That's somethin' my old man taught me.

Text.SourceString: Wow. Your life's a hive of activity.//Don't forget to take a breather and commune with Mother Nature.
Text.LocalizedString: Wow. Your life's a hive of activity.//Don't forget to take a breather and commune with Mother Nature.

Text.SourceString: Speak your heart's desires, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>And let nature decide your next steps. That's how I go about it.
Text.LocalizedString: Speak your heart's desires, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=normal>And let nature decide your next steps. That's how I go about it.

Text.SourceString: What a glorious day we're havin'!//I reckon it's gonna be a stellar week.
Text.LocalizedString: What a glorious day we're havin'!//I reckon it's gonna be a stellar week.

Text.SourceString: I just have this feelin' in my bones.
Text.LocalizedString: I just have this feelin' in my bones.

Text.SourceString: No doubt about it, the cows do seem to take kindly to my flute playin'.//It helps 'em wind down a bit.
Text.LocalizedString: No doubt about it, the cows do seem to take kindly to my flute playin'.//It helps 'em wind down a bit.

Text.SourceString: My friends <NpcName>Pablo</> and <NpcName>Rafael</> are very talented blacksmiths, bless their hearts.//<portrait=smile>They’re my go-to experts when the ranch needs any tools fixed.
Text.LocalizedString: My friends <NpcName>Pablo</> and <NpcName>Rafael</> are very talented blacksmiths, bless their hearts.//<portrait=smile>They’re my go-to experts when the ranch needs any tools fixed.

Text.SourceString: The boys make durable weapons too.//Mom always puts in a good word for 'em.
Text.LocalizedString: The boys make durable weapons too.//Mom always puts in a good word for 'em.

Text.SourceString: I don’t carry a weapon or heavy armor around in my bag, only wooden flutes.//Harmless instruments.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t carry a weapon or heavy armor around in my bag, only wooden flutes.//Harmless instruments.

Text.SourceString: And maybe a handful of soybeans.
Text.LocalizedString: And maybe a handful of soybeans.

Text.SourceString: You can collect wild vegetables and cook them.//Go ahead!
Text.LocalizedString: You can collect wild vegetables and cook them.//Go ahead!

Text.SourceString: Or if you’re anything like me, you could just eat 'em raw. Less work!
Text.LocalizedString: Or if you’re anything like me, you could just eat 'em raw. Less work!

Text.SourceString: Make sure to keep your animals inside when it rains, will you?
Text.LocalizedString: Make sure to keep your animals inside when it rains, will you?

Text.SourceString: I have no worries when I’m around you. You seem like a loving person.//<portrait=normal>You just have that aura.
Text.LocalizedString: I have no worries when I’m around you. You seem like a loving person.//<portrait=normal>You just have that aura.

Text.SourceString: Mom is a retired hunter, but she’s always on high alert.//<portrait=concerned>She’d go back into combat in a heartbeat, if necessary.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom is a retired hunter, but she’s always on high alert.//<portrait=concerned>She’d go back into combat in a heartbeat, if necessary.

Text.SourceString: I don’t know. Any emergency.//<portrait=sad>I won’t jinx it.//<portrait=laugh>Don’t you worry, <PlayerName>$player</>! We’ll be just fine.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t know. Any emergency.//<portrait=sad>I won’t jinx it.//<portrait=laugh>Don’t you worry, <PlayerName>$player</>! We’ll be just fine.

Text.SourceString: You can grow your own animal feed by growing grass on your farm.//<portrait=normal>It can save you a lot of money.
Text.LocalizedString: You can grow your own animal feed by growing grass on your farm.//<portrait=normal>It can save you a lot of money.

Text.SourceString: But grass doesn’t grow in Winter.//Fact is, most plants don't. So...//<portrait=laugh>That’s when the ranch comes in handy.
Text.LocalizedString: But grass doesn’t grow in Winter.//Fact is, most plants don't. So...//<portrait=laugh>That’s when the ranch comes in handy.

Text.SourceString: I don’t really go to the beach unless there’s an important event going on.//<portrait=sad>Yeah, no.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t really go to the beach unless there’s an important event going on.//<portrait=sad>Yeah, no.

Text.SourceString: No reason. I guess I just don’t have the drive to go to the beach that much.
Text.LocalizedString: No reason. I guess I just don’t have the drive to go to the beach that much.

Text.SourceString: Ah, I might go to Fishensips this weekend.//<portrait=normal>I don’t know.//Will you be there?
Text.LocalizedString: Ah, I might go to Fishensips this weekend.//<portrait=normal>I don’t know.//Will you be there?

Text.SourceString: Have you ever looked at the sky and wondered what’s out there?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever looked at the sky and wondered what’s out there?

Text.SourceString: I spend a lot of my free time doing just that.//<portrait=daydreaming>Looking at the sky, letting my mind wander.//<portrait=normal>This world sometimes feels too small for my imagination.
Text.LocalizedString: I spend a lot of my free time doing just that.//<portrait=daydreaming>Looking at the sky, letting my mind wander.//<portrait=normal>This world sometimes feels too small for my imagination.

Text.SourceString: I learned this from my granddad.//So, once you have animals, make sure you chat 'em up every day. That's all they're askin' for.//<portrait=concerned>And food. You get that, right?
Text.LocalizedString: I learned this from my granddad.//So, once you have animals, make sure you chat 'em up every day. That's all they're askin' for.//<portrait=concerned>And food. You get that, right?

Text.SourceString: Don't you forget to keep their bellies full!//<portrait=normal>I'm hopin' that bit's clear as day.
Text.LocalizedString: Don't you forget to keep their bellies full!//<portrait=normal>I'm hopin' that bit's clear as day.

Text.SourceString: It’s the weekend again!//<portrait=smile>Anything exciting happening?
Text.LocalizedString: It’s the weekend again!//<portrait=smile>Anything exciting happening?

Text.SourceString: Yeah, my week was good.//<portrait=normal>Same old, same old, though.//What about you?//I hope your week was good too.
Text.LocalizedString: Yeah, my week was good.//<portrait=normal>Same old, same old, though.//What about you?//I hope your week was good too.

Text.SourceString: Kombucha is the best drink to have with lunch. Love it, yeah?//Especially when it’s sunny out. It has that refreshing kick, you know?
Text.LocalizedString: Kombucha is the best drink to have with lunch. Love it, yeah?//Especially when it’s sunny out. It has that refreshing kick, you know?

Text.SourceString: I prefer to have my lunch break outdoors. Be one with nature, yeah? 'Course, that's when the weather's agreeable.
Text.LocalizedString: I prefer to have my lunch break outdoors. Be one with nature, yeah? 'Course, that's when the weather's agreeable.

Text.SourceString: Hmm... Times when my words don't quite cut it, I lean on my flute to do the speakin'.
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm... Times when my words don't quite cut it, I lean on my flute to do the speakin'.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, well... there just ain't no other way 'round it. Words alone just ain't enough.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, well... there just ain't no other way 'round it. Words alone just ain't enough.

Text.SourceString: I have to say I’m a little surprised to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to say I’m a little surprised to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: A pleasant surprise, that is. A very pleasant surprise.//As if the universe wants us to spend the day together. Do you believe in things like that?
Text.LocalizedString: A pleasant surprise, that is. A very pleasant surprise.//As if the universe wants us to spend the day together. Do you believe in things like that?

Text.SourceString: I have to say I’m a little surprised to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: I have to say I’m a little surprised to see you here, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: A pleasant surprise, that is. A very pleasant surprise.//As if the universe wants us to spend the day together. Do you believe in things like that?
Text.LocalizedString: A pleasant surprise, that is. A very pleasant surprise.//As if the universe wants us to spend the day together. Do you believe in things like that?

Text.SourceString: I’m not a fan of processed foods.//I read in some place they're cooked up to make us hooked on 'em.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a fan of processed foods.//I read in some place they're cooked up to make us hooked on 'em.

Text.SourceString: Ain't that a fright?
Text.LocalizedString: Ain't that a fright?

Text.SourceString: The more I think about us, folks, the sadder I get. We put chemicals in our food.//Some of us, we push others around for no good reason. Just ain't right.
Text.LocalizedString: The more I think about us, folks, the sadder I get. We put chemicals in our food.//Some of us, we push others around for no good reason. Just ain't right.

Text.SourceString: *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: *sighs*

Text.SourceString: I don’t like processed foods, but I’m not gonna lie, I eat 'em  once in a while.
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t like processed foods, but I’m not gonna lie, I eat 'em  once in a while.

Text.SourceString: I just get really sleepy afterward. Ain't a great feeling, not one bit. Blech!
Text.LocalizedString: I just get really sleepy afterward. Ain't a great feeling, not one bit. Blech!

Text.SourceString: I went to town yesterday and saw a drilling corporation is moving its offices to Coral Island.//<portrait=concerned>I’m disappointed, to be honest.
Text.LocalizedString: I went to town yesterday and saw a drilling corporation is moving its offices to Coral Island.//<portrait=concerned>I’m disappointed, to be honest.

Text.SourceString: It was a shock, really.//I had no idea they were buying properties here. What will they make of Coral Island, I wonder?
Text.LocalizedString: It was a shock, really.//I had no idea they were buying properties here. What will they make of Coral Island, I wonder?

Text.SourceString: I hope Pufferfish changes their mind.//<portrait=sad>All I sense from this is negativity.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope Pufferfish changes their mind.//<portrait=sad>All I sense from this is negativity.

Text.SourceString: Is Pufferfish building a mini golf area in front of their office?//<portrait=annoyed>Ugh… I kind of want to play.
Text.LocalizedString: Is Pufferfish building a mini golf area in front of their office?//<portrait=annoyed>Ugh… I kind of want to play.

Text.SourceString: Wild fruit and mushrooms are gifts of nature.//They’re so easy to find around here.
Text.LocalizedString: Wild fruit and mushrooms are gifts of nature.//They’re so easy to find around here.

Text.SourceString: Mom used to slay monsters for a living, but she's hung up her sword for now.//<portrait=normal>Reckons the island's peaceful enough these days, so she just keeps an eye on that cavern.//Wouldn't let me nowhere near that place as a kid. Monster infested, she said.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom used to slay monsters for a living, but she's hung up her sword for now.//<portrait=normal>Reckons the island's peaceful enough these days, so she just keeps an eye on that cavern.//Wouldn't let me nowhere near that place as a kid. Monster infested, she said.

Text.SourceString: My folks and I... We don't always see eye-to-eye on everything, but they respect my views, and that means a lot.//<portrait=normal>For example, my parents don’t celebrate birthdays, but they don’t force that view on me. I celebrate mine, all right!//Born and bred in Spring, on the 9th!
Text.LocalizedString: My folks and I... We don't always see eye-to-eye on everything, but they respect my views, and that means a lot.//<portrait=normal>For example, my parents don’t celebrate birthdays, but they don’t force that view on me. I celebrate mine, all right!//Born and bred in Spring, on the 9th!

Text.SourceString: Being a first-time farmer must be challenging. There’s a lot to get used to, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Being a first-time farmer must be challenging. There’s a lot to get used to, huh?

Text.SourceString: My folks, they had me when they were just young themselves.//Because of that, I feel like we’re speaking the same language most of the time.//There isn’t much of a generation gap.
Text.LocalizedString: My folks, they had me when they were just young themselves.//Because of that, I feel like we’re speaking the same language most of the time.//There isn’t much of a generation gap.

Text.SourceString: The gap? Oh, I just mean it’s easy to tell my parents how I feel about stuff.//Or you know, just to communicate in general.
Text.LocalizedString: The gap? Oh, I just mean it’s easy to tell my parents how I feel about stuff.//Or you know, just to communicate in general.

Text.SourceString: Another year has begun. These cherry blossoms are a beautiful reminder.
Text.LocalizedString: Another year has begun. These cherry blossoms are a beautiful reminder.

Text.SourceString: Are you close to <NPCName>Macy</>?//<portrait=normal>I believe it’s her birthday tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you close to <NPCName>Macy</>?//<portrait=normal>I believe it’s her birthday tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: She’s a beautiful soul with a big soft spot for animals.
Text.LocalizedString: She’s a beautiful soul with a big soft spot for animals.

Text.SourceString: Are you close to <NPCName>Macy</>?//<portrait=normal>I believe it’s her birthday tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you close to <NPCName>Macy</>?//<portrait=normal>I believe it’s her birthday tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: She’s a beautiful soul with a big soft spot for animals.
Text.LocalizedString: She’s a beautiful soul with a big soft spot for animals.

Text.SourceString: I try to stay away from animal products as much as I can.
Text.LocalizedString: I try to stay away from animal products as much as I can.

Text.SourceString: Had a bit of a morning. We had to nurse an injured cow.//<portrait=sad>She's fightin', bless her. I think she'll pull through.
Text.LocalizedString: Had a bit of a morning. We had to nurse an injured cow.//<portrait=sad>She's fightin', bless her. I think she'll pull through.

Text.SourceString: Has that ever happened at your farm?
Text.LocalizedString: Has that ever happened at your farm?

Text.SourceString: Spring is my favorite time of year!//<portrait=normal>The flowers are opening up, the fawns are learning to walk. It feels like everything is waking up after Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: Spring is my favorite time of year!//<portrait=normal>The flowers are opening up, the fawns are learning to walk. It feels like everything is waking up after Winter.

Text.SourceString: Havin' my birthday in Spring, now that's a blessing.//<portrait=daydreaming>It feels like nature is putting on a show for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Havin' my birthday in Spring, now that's a blessing.//<portrait=daydreaming>It feels like nature is putting on a show for me.

Text.SourceString: Even if I weren’t here, the natural world would keep on going without me.//<portrait=normal>Sounds a bit gloomy, I know, but there's a certain comfort in it for me.
Text.LocalizedString: Even if I weren’t here, the natural world would keep on going without me.//<portrait=normal>Sounds a bit gloomy, I know, but there's a certain comfort in it for me.

Text.SourceString: Have you planted any Spring flowers, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=laugh>Make sure your animals don’t snack on them!
Text.LocalizedString: Have you planted any Spring flowers, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=laugh>Make sure your animals don’t snack on them!

Text.SourceString: There are so many delicious things you can grow in Spring!//<portrait=daydreaming>My mouth is watering with all the taco possibilities…
Text.LocalizedString: There are so many delicious things you can grow in Spring!//<portrait=daydreaming>My mouth is watering with all the taco possibilities…

Text.SourceString: Spring is the time to plan for the year to come.//Have you taken stock of all your crops and animals yet?
Text.LocalizedString: Spring is the time to plan for the year to come.//Have you taken stock of all your crops and animals yet?

Text.SourceString: Good sense to keep things organized, mind you.
Text.LocalizedString: Good sense to keep things organized, mind you.

Text.SourceString: Can you hear it, <PlayerName>$player</>?//The trees, they're singin'. Buzzin' with joy that Spring's here at last.
Text.LocalizedString: Can you hear it, <PlayerName>$player</>?//The trees, they're singin'. Buzzin' with joy that Spring's here at last.

Text.SourceString: I’m playing along with the trees, <PlayerName>$player</>. Happy as can be.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m playing along with the trees, <PlayerName>$player</>. Happy as can be.

Text.SourceString: Hey, you wanna join me and listen to the birds? They’re so cheerful right now.
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, you wanna join me and listen to the birds? They’re so cheerful right now.

Text.SourceString: Nothin' like being able to have your lunch out in the open again.//I missed doing that in Winter.
Text.LocalizedString: Nothin' like being able to have your lunch out in the open again.//I missed doing that in Winter.

Text.SourceString: Why coop up indoors when there's all this beauty outside? Just look at all these blossoms!
Text.LocalizedString: Why coop up indoors when there's all this beauty outside? Just look at all these blossoms!

Text.SourceString: Finally, Spring!//<portrait=daydreaming>I welcome the sound of the creatures coming back to life.
Text.LocalizedString: Finally, Spring!//<portrait=daydreaming>I welcome the sound of the creatures coming back to life.

Text.SourceString: Look up, <PlayerName>$player</>! The birds are makin' their way back, one by one.//Ain't their songs just the sweetest thing?
Text.LocalizedString: Look up, <PlayerName>$player</>! The birds are makin' their way back, one by one.//Ain't their songs just the sweetest thing?

Text.SourceString: I think the daisies in Summer are nature telling us it’s happy and healthy. Don’t you think?
Text.LocalizedString: I think the daisies in Summer are nature telling us it’s happy and healthy. Don’t you think?

Text.SourceString: Since the days are longer in Summer, it’s nice to have all this time to spend outside.
Text.LocalizedString: Since the days are longer in Summer, it’s nice to have all this time to spend outside.

Text.SourceString: It’s hotter than I’d like for eating outside, but it’s much better than eating inside.//<portrait=daydreaming>Nothing beats eating in nature, not even air-conditioned rooms.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hotter than I’d like for eating outside, but it’s much better than eating inside.//<portrait=daydreaming>Nothing beats eating in nature, not even air-conditioned rooms.

Text.SourceString: Sure, the Summer heat makes my work harder, but I’d rather sweat it out surrounded by nature than stay inside.
Text.LocalizedString: Sure, the Summer heat makes my work harder, but I’d rather sweat it out surrounded by nature than stay inside.

Text.SourceString: I’m a little sad, friend. The trees are starting to lose their leaves, and the animals are leaving.//<portrait=normal>Well, at least I've still got the ranch animals for company.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m a little sad, friend. The trees are starting to lose their leaves, and the animals are leaving.//<portrait=normal>Well, at least I've still got the ranch animals for company.

Text.SourceString: Fall is a pretty busy season for farmers, I bet. All the harvesting to do.//<portrait=normal>My old man's got me all tied up preppin' the animals for Winter.//<portrait=laugh>I guess I’m busy in Fall too!
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is a pretty busy season for farmers, I bet. All the harvesting to do.//<portrait=normal>My old man's got me all tied up preppin' the animals for Winter.//<portrait=laugh>I guess I’m busy in Fall too!

Text.SourceString: I’m savoring all the time I can spend outside now.//<portrait=sad>In about a week, I won’t be able to enjoy the outdoors like this.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m savoring all the time I can spend outside now.//<portrait=sad>In about a week, I won’t be able to enjoy the outdoors like this.

Text.SourceString: Look up, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=concerned>A lot of birds are migrating south.//Goodbye, sweet birds.//<portrait=daydreaming>I’ll see you again in Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: Look up, <PlayerName>$player</>.//<portrait=concerned>A lot of birds are migrating south.//Goodbye, sweet birds.//<portrait=daydreaming>I’ll see you again in Spring.

Text.SourceString: Want some of my green tea, <PlayerName>$player</>? I always carry some in Fall. It’s a nice, quick warm-up when it’s chilly.
Text.LocalizedString: Want some of my green tea, <PlayerName>$player</>? I always carry some in Fall. It’s a nice, quick warm-up when it’s chilly.

Text.SourceString: Not gonna lie, Winter bums me out a bit. The trees are quiet, and a lot of animals are either hibernating or have migrated to somewhere warmer.
Text.LocalizedString: Not gonna lie, Winter bums me out a bit. The trees are quiet, and a lot of animals are either hibernating or have migrated to somewhere warmer.

Text.SourceString: I’m not a big fan of the cold.//It’s hard to eat your lunch outside when you’re constantly shivering.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m not a big fan of the cold.//It’s hard to eat your lunch outside when you’re constantly shivering.

Text.SourceString: I wish I could hibernate like the bears. Sleep through the cold Winter and wake up when it’s warm again in Spring.
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could hibernate like the bears. Sleep through the cold Winter and wake up when it’s warm again in Spring.

Text.SourceString: When it’s cold like this, there’s nothing like a cup of hot green tea to warm you up.
Text.LocalizedString: When it’s cold like this, there’s nothing like a cup of hot green tea to warm you up.

Text.SourceString: Winter makes me think of roasted almonds.//<portrait=normal>Hmm, maybe I’ll stop by <NPCName>Sam</>’s and buy some to roast over the fire.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter makes me think of roasted almonds.//<portrait=normal>Hmm, maybe I’ll stop by <NPCName>Sam</>’s and buy some to roast over the fire.

Text.SourceString: Winter is always so quiet.//Hear that? Basically nothing. Just faint music far, <Italic>far</> away.//Don’t worry, I hear it too. It’s nature’s music.
Text.LocalizedString: Winter is always so quiet.//Hear that? Basically nothing. Just faint music far, <Italic>far</> away.//Don’t worry, I hear it too. It’s nature’s music.

Text.SourceString: I can’t wait to hear the birds again, <PlayerName>$player</>. I miss their songs on my morning walks.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t wait to hear the birds again, <PlayerName>$player</>. I miss their songs on my morning walks.

Text.SourceString: It’s so cold that even a hot cup of green tea isn’t helping.//<portrait=sad>I should just head inside.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so cold that even a hot cup of green tea isn’t helping.//<portrait=sad>I should just head inside.

Text.SourceString: The hot spring sounds so good right now.
Text.LocalizedString: The hot spring sounds so good right now.

Text.SourceString: There’s a picture of me playing on your farm when I was maybe eight years old.//It’s hanging somewhere in our cabin.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a picture of me playing on your farm when I was maybe eight years old.//It’s hanging somewhere in our cabin.

Text.SourceString: This was back when it was still your grandparents’.
Text.LocalizedString: This was back when it was still your grandparents’.

Text.SourceString: The bugs are always thickest in Summer.//Just yesterday, found a wasp in the barn, took it outside.
Text.LocalizedString: The bugs are always thickest in Summer.//Just yesterday, found a wasp in the barn, took it outside.

Text.SourceString: It stung me, but I think it was just scared.
Text.LocalizedString: It stung me, but I think it was just scared.

Text.SourceString: The color of the lake is so beautiful this time of year.//When you splash, the water catches the sunlight, makin' tiny rainbows.
Text.LocalizedString: The color of the lake is so beautiful this time of year.//When you splash, the water catches the sunlight, makin' tiny rainbows.

Text.SourceString: Let’s go swimming there sometime!
Text.LocalizedString: Let’s go swimming there sometime!

Text.SourceString: You harvested any pineapples yet?//Heard they're somethin' special when grilled!
Text.LocalizedString: You harvested any pineapples yet?//Heard they're somethin' special when grilled!

Text.SourceString: Summer heat makes moving the animals twice as hard. It’s not so bad, though.//At least it’s already light when I get up in the morning!
Text.LocalizedString: Summer heat makes moving the animals twice as hard. It’s not so bad, though.//At least it’s already light when I get up in the morning!

Text.SourceString: But you sure wouldn't wanna be anywhere near me after work, phew!
Text.LocalizedString: But you sure wouldn't wanna be anywhere near me after work, phew!

Text.SourceString: Oopsie! Got a bit of pollen on my hat.//Lucky it didn't fall in my eyes.
Text.LocalizedString: Oopsie! Got a bit of pollen on my hat.//Lucky it didn't fall in my eyes.

Text.SourceString: Is there a flower nearby that I can brush it on?
Text.LocalizedString: Is there a flower nearby that I can brush it on?

Text.SourceString: Incredible how time flies, isn’t it?
Text.LocalizedString: Incredible how time flies, isn’t it?

Text.SourceString: I was shocked to wake up this morning and realize it’s already the 16th. *sighs*
Text.LocalizedString: I was shocked to wake up this morning and realize it’s already the 16th. *sighs*

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> is zoning out.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> is zoning out.]

Text.SourceString: Even though my parents don’t celebrate birthdays, they still love getting presents.
Text.LocalizedString: Even though my parents don’t celebrate birthdays, they still love getting presents.

Text.SourceString: If you want to win my mom over, she has a soft spot for flowers.
Text.LocalizedString: If you want to win my mom over, she has a soft spot for flowers.

Text.SourceString: Funbucket, bless his little feathered heart, is one of our ducks.//But <NPCName>Ben</> comes by often to help out with the animals, and they seem to have bonded. So now, Funbucket is his duck too.
Text.LocalizedString: Funbucket, bless his little feathered heart, is one of our ducks.//But <NPCName>Ben</> comes by often to help out with the animals, and they seem to have bonded. So now, Funbucket is his duck too.

Text.SourceString: This is the most beautiful foliage I’ve ever seen on Coral Island!
Text.LocalizedString: This is the most beautiful foliage I’ve ever seen on Coral Island!

Text.SourceString: I reckon I say that every year, but this time I mean it!
Text.LocalizedString: I reckon I say that every year, but this time I mean it!

Text.SourceString: I’m trying to catch as much sun as I can by the lake while it’s still Fall.//Once Winter comes, the sun is too weak to warm you up.

Text.SourceString: This island looks like a whole new place when it's covered in snow like this.

Text.SourceString: Can't for the life of me remember their name though.//They're shy little things, only bloomin' after sunset.

Text.SourceString: Are you going to the Winter Fair tomorrow?
Text.LocalizedString: Are you going to the Winter Fair tomorrow?

Text.SourceString: I like chatting with the merchants and sharing stories. They have an interesting view of the world.

Text.LocalizedString: Keep warm, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: Have you checked on your animals today?//<portrait=smile>They could use extra love on days like this.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you checked on your animals today?//<portrait=smile>They could use extra love on days like this.

Text.LocalizedString: Animals get cold too, especially when it’s snowing like this. Make sure to turn your heater on, okay?

Text.LocalizedString: I can imagine watching the snow as it falls.

Text.SourceString: What do you see when you see the snow, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: What do you see when you see the snow, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Very wise. I must agree. Keep going with whatever project you’re working on. You’re on to something big.

Text.LocalizedString: Stephen was stranded and had lost his left claw when <NPCName>Macy</> rescued him.//<portrait=normal>The last time I saw him, he was recovering quite well.

Text.LocalizedString: So many thoughts went into that art piece.//<portrait=daydreaming>When I look at it, I can feel conviction and hope deep down in my bones.

Text.SourceString: Are you planning to take home a new animal?//<portrait=normal>I can tell you which ones are the friendliest.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you planning to take home a new animal?//<portrait=normal>I can tell you which ones are the friendliest.

Text.SourceString: You can’t have Bessie, though.//<portrait=normal>She’s my best friend.//<portrait=laugh>My <Italic>Bessie</> friend!
Text.LocalizedString: You can’t have Bessie, though.//<portrait=normal>She’s my best friend.//<portrait=laugh>My <Italic>Bessie</> friend!

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> is staring into space.]//<portrait=concerned>What time is it?
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> is staring into space.]//<portrait=concerned>What time is it?

Text.SourceString: Oh no! Is it really that late already?//<portrait=normal>I didn’t mean to zone out for that long! Thanks for snapping me out of it, <PlayerName>$player</>.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh no! Is it really that late already?//<portrait=normal>I didn’t mean to zone out for that long! Thanks for snapping me out of it, <PlayerName>$player</>.

Text.SourceString: I found a gecko on the barn floor last week. It freaked out the cows a little, but I thought it was really cool!
Text.LocalizedString: I found a gecko on the barn floor last week. It freaked out the cows a little, but I thought it was really cool!

Text.SourceString: Do you ever daydream, <PlayerName>$player</>? It’s one of my bad habits.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you ever daydream, <PlayerName>$player</>? It’s one of my bad habits.

Text.SourceString: Well, I guess it’s not really bad. But I probably shouldn’t do it while I’m working, huh?
Text.LocalizedString: Well, I guess it’s not really bad. But I probably shouldn’t do it while I’m working, huh?

Text.SourceString: Animals that are taken care of well give the best milk, wool, and eggs.//The money from the sale sure keeps our local businesses afloat.
Text.LocalizedString: Animals that are taken care of well give the best milk, wool, and eggs.//The money from the sale sure keeps our local businesses afloat.

Text.SourceString: Sure, money's a fine thing, and no denying.//<portrait=concerned>But it shouldn’t be the only reason to be kind to animals.//<portrait=normal>They deserve love, just the same as any one of us does.
Text.LocalizedString: Sure, money's a fine thing, and no denying.//<portrait=concerned>But it shouldn’t be the only reason to be kind to animals.//<portrait=normal>They deserve love, just the same as any one of us does.

Text.SourceString: Say, how 'bout you join me for a spot of lunch down by the lake one of these days, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//<portrait=normal>It’s so peaceful there with the trees and the animals and everything.//I bet you’d like it.
Text.LocalizedString: Say, how 'bout you join me for a spot of lunch down by the lake one of these days, <PlayerName>$Player</>?//<portrait=normal>It’s so peaceful there with the trees and the animals and everything.//I bet you’d like it.

Text.SourceString: Do you check the weather forecast, <PlayerName>$player</>?//It's a good habit to have. Animals need shelter from the rain just like humans do.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you check the weather forecast, <PlayerName>$player</>?//It's a good habit to have. Animals need shelter from the rain just like humans do.

Text.SourceString: It’s good to leave your plants out in the rain, though!//<portrait=laugh>Weird how nature works.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s good to leave your plants out in the rain, though!//<portrait=laugh>Weird how nature works.

Text.SourceString: Animals are fine listeners.//Even though they don't have a way of talking back to us, I always feel like they're taking in every word I say.
Text.LocalizedString: Animals are fine listeners.//Even though they don't have a way of talking back to us, I always feel like they're taking in every word I say.

Text.SourceString: Or maybe they’re just waiting to see if I pull a snack out of my pocket.//<portrait=smile>That’s also possible.
Text.LocalizedString: Or maybe they’re just waiting to see if I pull a snack out of my pocket.//<portrait=smile>That’s also possible.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>, whoa! Be careful!//<portrait=concerned>You almost stepped on that ant.
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>, whoa! Be careful!//<portrait=concerned>You almost stepped on that ant.

Text.SourceString: Do you have a favorite animal, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you have a favorite animal, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Me? I’m not allowed to pick a favorite. I love them all equally.
Text.LocalizedString: Me? I’m not allowed to pick a favorite. I love them all equally.

Text.SourceString: I lent my best tool to <NPCName>Ben</>, but he hasn’t given it back yet. Should I ask him about it?
Text.LocalizedString: I lent my best tool to <NPCName>Ben</>, but he hasn’t given it back yet. Should I ask him about it?

Text.SourceString: Oh well. He’ll probably return it when he’s done.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh well. He’ll probably return it when he’s done.

Text.SourceString: This might sound weird, but being here right now feels as natural as…well, nature.//<portrait=daydreaming>I can’t think of anywhere else I’d rather be.
Text.LocalizedString: This might sound weird, but being here right now feels as natural as…well, nature.//<portrait=daydreaming>I can’t think of anywhere else I’d rather be.

Text.SourceString: I always bring extra food for the ants when I come here.
Text.LocalizedString: I always bring extra food for the ants when I come here.

Text.SourceString: Working in the rain can be challenging, but I don’t mind.//At least it goes a long way in washin' all that muck and pollution right outta the air.
Text.LocalizedString: Working in the rain can be challenging, but I don’t mind.//At least it goes a long way in washin' all that muck and pollution right outta the air.

Text.SourceString: See, on the one hand, rain's a blessin' for plants and animals in need of a clean drink.//<portrait=sad>On the other hand, it means I can’t eat my lunch outside.
Text.LocalizedString: See, on the one hand, rain's a blessin' for plants and animals in need of a clean drink.//<portrait=sad>On the other hand, it means I can’t eat my lunch outside.

Text.SourceString: I can’t play my flute outside, either.
Text.LocalizedString: I can’t play my flute outside, either.

Text.SourceString: Dang, it's been a steady downpour since this morning.//<portrait=sad>The animals aren’t going to be happy about being cooped up all day.
Text.LocalizedString: Dang, it's been a steady downpour since this morning.//<portrait=sad>The animals aren’t going to be happy about being cooped up all day.

Text.SourceString: I hope it clears up tomorrow. I really want to eat in the forest again.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope it clears up tomorrow. I really want to eat in the forest again.

Text.SourceString: There’s not much you can do outside when it’s raining, so I like to pass the time in here.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s not much you can do outside when it’s raining, so I like to pass the time in here.

Text.SourceString: Now, don't get me wrong, nature's a spectacle to behold, I’d rather not be soaking wet while I do it.
Text.LocalizedString: Now, don't get me wrong, nature's a spectacle to behold, I’d rather not be soaking wet while I do it.

Text.SourceString: Oh, <PlayerName>$player</>! Have you checked the weather forecast yet?//I'm crossin' my fingers it ain't callin' for more rain tomorrow.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, <PlayerName>$player</>! Have you checked the weather forecast yet?//I'm crossin' my fingers it ain't callin' for more rain tomorrow.

Text.SourceString: It’s not <Italic>really</> reliable, but hey… We don’t have anything better.//I’ll have to take a look later.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s not <Italic>really</> reliable, but hey… We don’t have anything better.//I’ll have to take a look later.

Text.SourceString: I guess leaving animals out in the rain might make 'em cleaner, but it also gets 'em mighty upset.//<portrait=normal>You should always be sure your animals have a dry place to stay when it rains.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess leaving animals out in the rain might make 'em cleaner, but it also gets 'em mighty upset.//<portrait=normal>You should always be sure your animals have a dry place to stay when it rains.

Text.SourceString: I sleep so well when it’s raining.//<portrait=daydreaming>The <Italic>tap tap tap</> on my window is strangely comforting.
Text.LocalizedString: I sleep so well when it’s raining.//<portrait=daydreaming>The <Italic>tap tap tap</> on my window is strangely comforting.

Text.SourceString: Let me tell you a tale of the forest.//One dark, rainy night in the woods, something shivered behind a tree.//<portrait=concerned>It was neither man nor beast.//<portrait=annoyed>It was…a ghost!
Text.LocalizedString: Let me tell you a tale of the forest.//One dark, rainy night in the woods, something shivered behind a tree.//<portrait=concerned>It was neither man nor beast.//<portrait=annoyed>It was…a ghost!

Text.SourceString: Did you like my dramatic voice?//<portrait=laugh>Maybe I should take up acting!
Text.LocalizedString: Did you like my dramatic voice?//<portrait=laugh>Maybe I should take up acting!

Text.SourceString: This storm is really nasty, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=concerned>You shouldn’t be out in it!
Text.LocalizedString: This storm is really nasty, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=concerned>You shouldn’t be out in it!

Text.SourceString: Keep an eye on your crops and animals!//They might blow away if you’re not careful!
Text.LocalizedString: Keep an eye on your crops and animals!//They might blow away if you’re not careful!

Text.SourceString: C'mon now, <PlayerName>$player</>, let’s get you inside. Nighttime storms ain't nothin' to trifle with.//You can’t see if something’s flying through the air at you.
Text.LocalizedString: C'mon now, <PlayerName>$player</>, let’s get you inside. Nighttime storms ain't nothin' to trifle with.//You can’t see if something’s flying through the air at you.

Text.SourceString: Truth be told,I really shouldn’t be out in weather such as this, but curiosity got the better of me.//<portrait=smile>I wanted to see nature’s power firsthand!
Text.LocalizedString: Truth be told,I really shouldn’t be out in weather such as this, but curiosity got the better of me.//<portrait=smile>I wanted to see nature’s power firsthand!

Text.SourceString: To be safe inside, with a roof over my head during a storm… It makes me feel very grateful.
Text.LocalizedString: To be safe inside, with a roof over my head during a storm… It makes me feel very grateful.

Text.SourceString: Hmm… Just look at her go…
Text.LocalizedString: Hmm… Just look at her go…

Text.SourceString: Oh! My apologies there.//<portrait=normal>I sort of got lost in the swirling wind.//<portrait=laugh>It's all very theatrical, don't you think?
Text.LocalizedString: Oh! My apologies there.//<portrait=normal>I sort of got lost in the swirling wind.//<portrait=laugh>It's all very theatrical, don't you think?

Text.SourceString: I wish I could still see the storm.//<portrait=normal>It was so much fun to watch while it was light!
Text.LocalizedString: I wish I could still see the storm.//<portrait=normal>It was so much fun to watch while it was light!

Text.SourceString: You still gotta make your way home, right? Be careful out there.//Nature's not one for playin' jokes.
Text.LocalizedString: You still gotta make your way home, right? Be careful out there.//Nature's not one for playin' jokes.

Text.SourceString: You best come visit tomorrow, let me know you made it home safe and sound, okay?
Text.LocalizedString: You best come visit tomorrow, let me know you made it home safe and sound, okay?

Text.SourceString: Lots of folks find snow a sight to behold, but all it does for me is remind me of what's all buried beneath.//<portrait=sad>Plants, baby animals, folks…
Text.LocalizedString: Lots of folks find snow a sight to behold, but all it does for me is remind me of what's all buried beneath.//<portrait=sad>Plants, baby animals, folks…

Text.SourceString: I guess it is kind of funny when it piles up on the cows’ backs.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess it is kind of funny when it piles up on the cows’ backs.

Text.SourceString: Now, where are those Winter seeds I left lying around?//I hope they didn’t get buried in the snow.
Text.LocalizedString: Now, where are those Winter seeds I left lying around?//I hope they didn’t get buried in the snow.

Text.SourceString: Gotta start gettin' ready for Spring, I tell ya.
Text.LocalizedString: Gotta start gettin' ready for Spring, I tell ya.

Text.SourceString: Snow is part of nature, but it’s not my favorite part.//<portrait=laugh>I’d rather be stretched out under the Spring sun than slipping on this ice.
Text.LocalizedString: Snow is part of nature, but it’s not my favorite part.//<portrait=laugh>I’d rather be stretched out under the Spring sun than slipping on this ice.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad I’m not out there working in that slush.//<portrait=annoyed>I don’t like it, the animals don’t like it. It’s a bad time all around.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad I’m not out there working in that slush.//<portrait=annoyed>I don’t like it, the animals don’t like it. It’s a bad time all around.

Text.SourceString: I hope this snow stops tomorrow.//Might go diggin' for root veggies after work.
Text.LocalizedString: I hope this snow stops tomorrow.//Might go diggin' for root veggies after work.

Text.SourceString: *shivering* Someone light a fire! I’m freezing in here!
Text.LocalizedString: *shivering* Someone light a fire! I’m freezing in here!

Text.SourceString: Got a blanket on you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=concerned>No?//<portrait=normal>Well, that's alright then.
Text.LocalizedString: Got a blanket on you, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=concerned>No?//<portrait=normal>Well, that's alright then.

Text.SourceString: Is it just me, or does snow make Winter nights twice as cold?
Text.LocalizedString: Is it just me, or does snow make Winter nights twice as cold?

Text.SourceString: Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>! Watch where you step.//<portrait=normal>You never know where you’ll find manure!
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>! Watch where you step.//<portrait=normal>You never know where you’ll find manure!

Text.SourceString: It's cozy in here, ain't it?//<portrait=normal>I think my grandparents did a fine job building the place.
Text.LocalizedString: It's cozy in here, ain't it?//<portrait=normal>I think my grandparents did a fine job building the place.

Text.SourceString: I feel like I never stop cleaning in here, but I don’t mind.//If it keeps the animals happy, well, that's all the payment I need.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel like I never stop cleaning in here, but I don’t mind.//If it keeps the animals happy, well, that's all the payment I need.

Text.SourceString: Just you remember to keep your barn spick and span.
Text.LocalizedString: Just you remember to keep your barn spick and span.

Text.SourceString: Sometimes, Bessie’s hard to work with, but other days, she’s sweet and gentle.//<portrait=laugh>She’s got such a strong personality.
Text.LocalizedString: Sometimes, Bessie’s hard to work with, but other days, she’s sweet and gentle.//<portrait=laugh>She’s got such a strong personality.

Text.SourceString: Might sound a touch offbeat, but I truly believe animals get what we're sayin'.
Text.LocalizedString: Might sound a touch offbeat, but I truly believe animals get what we're sayin'.

Text.SourceString: Have you ever looked into an animal’s eyes and wondered what they’re thinking or what they’d say if they could talk?//<portrait=daydreaming>That's a thought that'll keep me occupied for hours.
Text.LocalizedString: Have you ever looked into an animal’s eyes and wondered what they’re thinking or what they’d say if they could talk?//<portrait=daydreaming>That's a thought that'll keep me occupied for hours.

Text.SourceString: Are you here to get a tool fixed too?//It’s so nice to chat with <NPCName>Pablo</> and <NPCName>Rafael</> while they're workin'.
Text.LocalizedString: Are you here to get a tool fixed too?//It’s so nice to chat with <NPCName>Pablo</> and <NPCName>Rafael</> while they're workin'.

Text.SourceString: You should talk to <NPCName>Pablo</> about getting some upgrades done.//<portrait=normal>I know how hard you work.//Upgrades really make ranch work easier!
Text.LocalizedString: You should talk to <NPCName>Pablo</> about getting some upgrades done.//<portrait=normal>I know how hard you work.//Upgrades really make ranch work easier!

Text.SourceString: Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>. Is it just me, or does everything feel quieter around here?
Text.LocalizedString: Hey, <PlayerName>$player</>. Is it just me, or does everything feel quieter around here?

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> is lost in thought.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> is lost in thought.]

Text.SourceString: My old man sent me to buy somethin' here, but I'll be darned if I know what I'm lookin' for.
Text.LocalizedString: My old man sent me to buy somethin' here, but I'll be darned if I know what I'm lookin' for.

Text.SourceString: Do you know what an “automatic despiffer” is?//No? Well, at least I’m not the only one.//<portrait=concerned>I’ll have to figure out something to tell my old man.
Text.LocalizedString: Do you know what an “automatic despiffer” is?//No? Well, at least I’m not the only one.//<portrait=concerned>I’ll have to figure out something to tell my old man.

Text.SourceString: Sure am glad I'm not out in the pouring rain today.//I don’t mind the rain itself, but trying to wrangle the animals while I’m all wet isn’t my idea of a good time.
Text.LocalizedString: Sure am glad I'm not out in the pouring rain today.//I don’t mind the rain itself, but trying to wrangle the animals while I’m all wet isn’t my idea of a good time.

Text.SourceString: Well hey there, <PlayerName>$player</>!//I reckon Mom must've let you in.
Text.LocalizedString: Well hey there, <PlayerName>$player</>!//I reckon Mom must've let you in.

Text.SourceString: Or did you let yourself in? That's alright by me.//You’re family.
Text.LocalizedString: Or did you let yourself in? That's alright by me.//You’re family.

Text.SourceString: It’s time for a snack! I love the way good smells fill up the whole house.//<portrait=normal>It makes me happy that it’s such a small place.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s time for a snack! I love the way good smells fill up the whole house.//<portrait=normal>It makes me happy that it’s such a small place.

Text.SourceString: Have you learned to cook anything tasty?
Text.LocalizedString: Have you learned to cook anything tasty?

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> appears to be sleeping.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> appears to be sleeping.]

Text.SourceString: I’m trying to figure out this flute melody, but I’m having a hard time.//<portrait=sad>Sometimes the notes seem to jump off the page and float away.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m trying to figure out this flute melody, but I’m having a hard time.//<portrait=sad>Sometimes the notes seem to jump off the page and float away.

Text.SourceString: It’s hard to stay focused when I get stuck.//It makes me want to do something else instead.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s hard to stay focused when I get stuck.//It makes me want to do something else instead.

Text.SourceString: This is a great place to forage for mushrooms and wild veggies.
Text.LocalizedString: This is a great place to forage for mushrooms and wild veggies.

Text.SourceString: You can also cook wild vegetables, by the way. They make great meals.
Text.LocalizedString: You can also cook wild vegetables, by the way. They make great meals.

Text.SourceString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> is lost in thought.]
Text.LocalizedString: [<NpcName>Kenny</> is lost in thought.]

Text.SourceString: It’s so nice to come here and hang out in the evenings.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s so nice to come here and hang out in the evenings.

Text.SourceString: Building a relationship is like growing a flower. It should happen organically.//You can’t force it. Relationships are fragile and beautiful.
Text.LocalizedString: Building a relationship is like growing a flower. It should happen organically.//You can’t force it. Relationships are fragile and beautiful.

Text.SourceString: Some relationships ain't meant to last long. They wilt when it's time.//Remember to enjoy it while it's in bloom, now.
Text.LocalizedString: Some relationships ain't meant to last long. They wilt when it's time.//Remember to enjoy it while it's in bloom, now.

Text.SourceString: A friend asked me if I’d ever seen anything weird in the forest. I told her yeah.//But I don’t go looking for it.//<portrait=smile>If it’s there, it’s there.
Text.LocalizedString: A friend asked me if I’d ever seen anything weird in the forest. I told her yeah.//But I don’t go looking for it.//<portrait=smile>If it’s there, it’s there.

Text.SourceString: There are some things in life we’re supposed to know and some we ain't.//<portrait=normal>The mystery, it's part of the beauty, don't you think?
Text.LocalizedString: There are some things in life we’re supposed to know and some we ain't.//<portrait=normal>The mystery, it's part of the beauty, don't you think?

Text.SourceString: This place has eyes.//It’s watching. Listening to us.
Text.LocalizedString: This place has eyes.//It’s watching. Listening to us.

Text.SourceString: To me, the most exciting part of life is not knowing what’s going to happen in the future.//That sense of uncertainty grabs my heart.
Text.LocalizedString: To me, the most exciting part of life is not knowing what’s going to happen in the future.//That sense of uncertainty grabs my heart.

Text.SourceString: Who knows, you may become a rancher full time and stop farming altogether.//Or maybe you’ll start performing at the Tavern with <NpcName>Theo</>. Can't never tell.
Text.LocalizedString: Who knows, you may become a rancher full time and stop farming altogether.//Or maybe you’ll start performing at the Tavern with <NpcName>Theo</>. Can't never tell.

Text.SourceString: There’s a small river inside the cavern that connects to the deep part of the forest.
Text.LocalizedString: There’s a small river inside the cavern that connects to the deep part of the forest.

Text.SourceString: The area's also accessible from Beluga Bay. It's a longer route, but the road is wide.
Text.LocalizedString: The area's also accessible from Beluga Bay. It's a longer route, but the road is wide.

Text.SourceString: You know, I don’t tell you this enough.//But I really like running into you.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, I don’t tell you this enough.//But I really like running into you.

Text.SourceString: Your aura is calming.//<portrait=daydreaming>Like the first bloom of cherry blossoms.
Text.LocalizedString: Your aura is calming.//<portrait=daydreaming>Like the first bloom of cherry blossoms.

Text.SourceString: You know, I don’t tell you this enough.//But I really like running into you.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, I don’t tell you this enough.//But I really like running into you.

Text.SourceString: Your aura is calming.//<portrait=daydreaming>Like the warm scent of roasted pumpkin.
Text.LocalizedString: Your aura is calming.//<portrait=daydreaming>Like the warm scent of roasted pumpkin.

Text.SourceString: That’s a nice Summer outfit you got, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//I should get something like that. What do you think?
Text.LocalizedString: That’s a nice Summer outfit you got, <PlayerName>$Player</>.//I should get something like that. What do you think?

Text.SourceString: I learned how to play pool from <NpcName>Pablo</>. Taught me everything I know.//<portrait=happy>That man is a legend, bless his heart.
Text.LocalizedString: I learned how to play pool from <NpcName>Pablo</>. Taught me everything I know.//<portrait=happy>That man is a legend, bless his heart.

Text.SourceString: Drink on me, cutie?
Text.LocalizedString: Drink on me, cutie?

Text.SourceString: Drink on me, buddy?
Text.LocalizedString: Drink on me, buddy?

Text.SourceString: Happy Wednesday, <PlayerName>$player</>!
Text.LocalizedString: Happy Wednesday, <PlayerName>$player</>!

Text.SourceString: Happy Friday, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=concerned>Er, um… It’s already Saturday. Oops!
Text.LocalizedString: Happy Friday, <PlayerName>$player</>!//<portrait=concerned>Er, um… It’s already Saturday. Oops!

Text.SourceString: The first step to having healthy animals is to feed them daily, of course.//That’s the basic stuff.
Text.LocalizedString: The first step to having healthy animals is to feed them daily, of course.//That’s the basic stuff.

Text.SourceString: You <Italic>do</> know that, right? The feeding animals bit?//<portrait=happy>Oh good, good! I know you know. Just making sure. That’s all.
Text.LocalizedString: You <Italic>do</> know that, right? The feeding animals bit?//<portrait=happy>Oh good, good! I know you know. Just making sure. That’s all.

Text.SourceString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Seeing you… They’re my favorite things.
Text.LocalizedString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Seeing you… They’re my favorite things.

Text.SourceString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Running into you… They’re my favorite things.
Text.LocalizedString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Running into you… They’re my favorite things.

Text.SourceString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Running into you… They’re my favorite things.
Text.LocalizedString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Running into you… They’re my favorite things.

Text.SourceString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Seeing you… They’re my favorite things.
Text.LocalizedString: All this – the blooming flowers, the mesmerizing sound of the rain.//Seeing you… They’re my favorite things.

Text.SourceString: Hope your weekend was good.
Text.LocalizedString: Hope your weekend was good.

Text.SourceString: It’s lovely to see you today. The highlight of my day.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s lovely to see you today. The highlight of my day.

Text.SourceString: You know, we don’t hang out enough. No pressure, though. I know you’re busy.
Text.LocalizedString: You know, we don’t hang out enough. No pressure, though. I know you’re busy.

Text.SourceString: Whatever you need to do. Please take your time.//If you want company, you know where to find me.
Text.LocalizedString: Whatever you need to do. Please take your time.//If you want company, you know where to find me.

Text.SourceString: I'll probably take over the ranch someday, just like my dad did.//And his mom before him.
Text.LocalizedString: I'll probably take over the ranch someday, just like my dad did.//And his mom before him.

Text.SourceString: It’s in my blood to take care of these animals.
Text.LocalizedString: It’s in my blood to take care of these animals.

Text.SourceString: What I really want? What do you mean by that?
Text.LocalizedString: What I really want? What do you mean by that?

Text.SourceString: Oh, well, this is what I want. A quiet and simple life is all.//Fancy things don’t make me happy, <PlayerName>$player</>. Sittin' behind a desk for forty-plus hours a week wouldn't give me the same satisfaction as takin' care of the ranch.
Text.LocalizedString: Oh, well, this is what I want. A quiet and simple life is all.//Fancy things don’t make me happy, <PlayerName>$player</>. Sittin' behind a desk for forty-plus hours a week wouldn't give me the same satisfaction as takin' care of the ranch.

Text.SourceString: I always try to educate myself on animal health from books and the internet.//<portrait=concerned>I read a lot of things online. Some things are straight-up odd, I have to say.
Text.LocalizedString: I always try to educate myself on animal health from books and the internet.//<portrait=concerned>I read a lot of things online. Some things are straight-up odd, I have to say.

Text.SourceString: I went into the cavern last week and got attacked by giant lava spiders! Phew.//I must've spooked 'em good.
Text.LocalizedString: I went into the cavern last week and got attacked by giant lava spiders! Phew.//I must've spooked 'em good.

Text.SourceString: I almost passed out trying to get them off me!
Text.LocalizedString: I almost passed out trying to get them off me!

Text.SourceString: I don't like carryin' weapons.//If I'm attacked, then I'm attacked. It's all right.
Text.LocalizedString: I don't like carryin' weapons.//If I'm attacked, then I'm attacked. It's all right.

Text.SourceString: I’m glad you moved to Coral Island, <PlayerName>$player</>. If I could keep you all for myself, I totally would.
Text.LocalizedString: I’m glad you moved to Coral Island, <PlayerName>$player</>. If I could keep you all for myself, I totally would.

Text.SourceString: But it wouldn't be fair to deprive the world of you, darlin'.
Text.LocalizedString: But it wouldn't be fair to deprive the world of you, darlin'.

Text.SourceString: I consider myself lucky. My parents didn’t force their dreams on me.
Text.LocalizedString: I consider myself lucky. My parents didn’t force their dreams on me.

Text.SourceString: I feel bad that my friend has that expectation imposed on him.//And he said the worst part is his parents mean well, which leaves him with nobody to blame.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel bad that my friend has that expectation imposed on him.//And he said the worst part is his parents mean well, which leaves him with nobody to blame.

Text.SourceString: Ahh...smell that? That's the scent of Coral Island. Hope and dreams.
Text.LocalizedString: Ahh...smell that? That's the scent of Coral Island. Hope and dreams.

Text.SourceString: There might’ve been some cow smells mixed in there too.
Text.LocalizedString: There might’ve been some cow smells mixed in there too.

Text.SourceString: Do they have to be so…abrupt? Our meetings.//It feels like I could use a little more time with you.
Text.LocalizedString: Do they have to be so…abrupt? Our meetings.//It feels like I could use a little more time with you.

Text.SourceString: Well, if you don’t mind, we could certainly arrange a more, errr, private rendezvous.//<portrait=happy>I want to be able to share my soul with you without time constraints.//Send me a letter, darlin'.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, if you don’t mind, we could certainly arrange a more, errr, private rendezvous.//<portrait=happy>I want to be able to share my soul with you without time constraints.//Send me a letter, darlin'.

Text.SourceString: I was thinking about using the extra room in the ranch.//Havin' my own little space with my stuff in it.
Text.LocalizedString: I was thinking about using the extra room in the ranch.//Havin' my own little space with my stuff in it.

Text.SourceString: I guess you could call it moving out.//<portrait=laugh>Movin' a whole ten minutes away from home.
Text.LocalizedString: I guess you could call it moving out.//<portrait=laugh>Movin' a whole ten minutes away from home.

Text.SourceString: I told my folks they can count on me to take care of the ranch, no matter what happens.//I won’t ever let it fall into someone else’s hands.
Text.LocalizedString: I told my folks they can count on me to take care of the ranch, no matter what happens.//I won’t ever let it fall into someone else’s hands.

Text.SourceString: Near the cavern? Sorry, I don’t know much about ruins.
Text.LocalizedString: Near the cavern? Sorry, I don’t know much about ruins.

Text.SourceString: Mom hasn’t told me much about them.
Text.LocalizedString: Mom hasn’t told me much about them.

Text.SourceString: Fall is giving you a magnificent glow today.//<portrait=blushing>I hope your day so far has been as good as you look.
Text.LocalizedString: Fall is giving you a magnificent glow today.//<portrait=blushing>I hope your day so far has been as good as you look.

Text.SourceString: Goin' on an adventure, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Goin' on an adventure, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: Goin' for a dip, <PlayerName>$player</>?
Text.LocalizedString: Goin' for a dip, <PlayerName>$player</>?

Text.SourceString: One of our cows at the ranch gave birth yesterday!//<portrait=normal>We have a brand-new calf to take care of. Got any suggestions for a name?
Text.LocalizedString: One of our cows at the ranch gave birth yesterday!//<portrait=normal>We have a brand-new calf to take care of. Got any suggestions for a name?

Text.SourceString: I was thinking Bessie Junior, but Dad doesn’t agree with me.
Text.LocalizedString: I was thinking Bessie Junior, but Dad doesn’t agree with me.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>! It’s good to–//Wait! Don’t move!
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>! It’s good to–//Wait! Don’t move!

Text.SourceString: There was a spider on your shoulder!//<portrait=normal>Is he your friend, or was he just along for the ride?//It’s okay, little guy. I won’t hurt you.
Text.LocalizedString: There was a spider on your shoulder!//<portrait=normal>Is he your friend, or was he just along for the ride?//It’s okay, little guy. I won’t hurt you.

Text.SourceString: Do you ever just wonder what’s out there, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=daydreaming>What kind of amazin' wonders and new friends are out there, just beyond our reach?
Text.LocalizedString: Do you ever just wonder what’s out there, <PlayerName>$player</>?//<portrait=daydreaming>What kind of amazin' wonders and new friends are out there, just beyond our reach?

Text.SourceString: Even though I'm happy here, I think 'bout it a lot.
Text.LocalizedString: Even though I'm happy here, I think 'bout it a lot.

Text.SourceString: <PlayerName>$player</>, I– Oh no, I stepped on a worm!
Text.LocalizedString: <PlayerName>$player</>, I– Oh no, I stepped on a worm!

Text.SourceString: I feel horrible.//<portrait=concerned>Will you help me bury it? No animal deserves to be stepped on, even the littlest ones.
Text.LocalizedString: I feel horrible.//<portrait=concerned>Will you help me bury it? No animal deserves to be stepped on, even the littlest ones.

Text.SourceString: I might go to <NPCName>Sam</>’s later. Do you need anything?//I can pick you up some flour or… What do you need?
Text.LocalizedString: I might go to <NPCName>Sam</>’s later. Do you need anything?//I can pick you up some flour or… What do you need?

Text.SourceString: I like this place. Nice and cold inside.
Text.LocalizedString: I like this place. Nice and cold inside.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Luke</> has an electric flute here.//I was thinking of getting it, but I don’t think I’d be disciplined enough to recharge the battery.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Luke</> has an electric flute here.//I was thinking of getting it, but I don’t think I’d be disciplined enough to recharge the battery.

Text.SourceString: I just can’t get this song right.//<portrait=sad>I’ve been working on it for weeks, but it’s not going well.
Text.LocalizedString: I just can’t get this song right.//<portrait=sad>I’ve been working on it for weeks, but it’s not going well.

Text.SourceString: You want to help me? That’s kind of you.//<portrait=normal>It’s, uh, something I have to do on my own, though. Unless you can read my mind. Ha ha.
Text.LocalizedString: You want to help me? That’s kind of you.//<portrait=normal>It’s, uh, something I have to do on my own, though. Unless you can read my mind. Ha ha.

Text.SourceString: Some of these trees have been here for a hundred years or more.//They’ll probably be here a hundred years after you and I are gone, too.
Text.LocalizedString: Some of these trees have been here for a hundred years or more.//They’ll probably be here a hundred years after you and I are gone, too.

Text.SourceString: That might sound depressing, but I think it’s pretty romantic, actually.//<portrait=daydreaming>Old trees, the sentinels of the forest. It’s like something out of a fairy tale.
Text.LocalizedString: That might sound depressing, but I think it’s pretty romantic, actually.//<portrait=daydreaming>Old trees, the sentinels of the forest. It’s like something out of a fairy tale.

Text.SourceString: What’s your favorite drink? Mine’s green tea.//<NpcName>Frank</> here can whip up just about any drink ya fancy. He's quite the master behind that bar.
Text.LocalizedString: What’s your favorite drink? Mine’s green tea.//<NpcName>Frank</> here can whip up just about any drink ya fancy. He's quite the master behind that bar.

Text.SourceString: Kombucha is great too. But I don’t think they sell any here.
Text.LocalizedString: Kombucha is great too. But I don’t think they sell any here.

Text.SourceString: I just had my dinner, and I’m <Italic>starving</>. What’s good here?
Text.LocalizedString: I just had my dinner, and I’m <Italic>starving</>. What’s good here?

Text.SourceString: Well, ain't this a nice way to end the day, takin' a moment to relax and unwind.
Text.LocalizedString: Well, ain't this a nice way to end the day, takin' a moment to relax and unwind.

Text.SourceString: I ran into <NpcName>Joko</> a couple of times by the creek near <NPCName>Ben</>’s caravan. He seems to like fishing there.//Oh, I was on my way to the hot spring.
Text.LocalizedString: I ran into <NpcName>Joko</> a couple of times by the creek near <NPCName>Ben</>’s caravan. He seems to like fishing there.//Oh, I was on my way to the hot spring.

Text.SourceString: <NpcName>Joko</> takes his son fishing with him.//Reminds me of my own childhood with my old man.
Text.LocalizedString: <NpcName>Joko</> takes his son fishing with him.//Reminds me of my own childhood with my old man.

Text.SourceString: Where do people go in Summer? It seems like it’s not as lively out right now.//<portrait=happy>Ah, right. They’re probably at the beach.
Text.LocalizedString: Where do people go in Summer? It seems like it’s not as lively out right now.//<portrait=happy>Ah, right. They’re probably at the beach.

Text.SourceString: My hat keeps me cool.
Text.LocalizedString: My hat keeps me cool.

Text.SourceString: Is pumpkin carving still a thing around here?//I remember carving pumpkins when I was in grade school. We got to display them at the town fair.//<portrait=happy>Right, right. The Harvest Festival!
Text.LocalizedString: Is pumpkin carving still a thing around here?//I remember carving pumpkins when I was in grade school. We got to display them at the town fair.//<portrait=happy>Right, right. The Harvest Festival!

Text.SourceString: I found this green jacket in one of Mom’s chests.//Can you believe it?
Text.LocalizedString: I found this green jacket in one of Mom’s chests.//Can you believe it?

Text.SourceString: I don’t usually wear red. You see, I like to blend in with the forest.//This sweater makes me pop.//<portrait=happy>But it was free, so hey, what can I say?
Text.LocalizedString: I don’t usually wear red. You see, I like to blend in with the forest.//This sweater makes me pop.//<portrait=happy>But it was free, so hey, what can I say?

Text.SourceString: My hat, well, it keeps me warm when the chill of Winter sets in.//Gotta make sure to stay cozy.
Text.LocalizedString: My hat, well, it keeps me warm when the chill of Winter sets in.//Gotta make sure to stay cozy.

Text.SourceString: I only have one hat.//<portrait=happy>And truth be told, it's all I need, so I see no point in hoarding more.
Text.LocalizedString: I only have one hat.//<portrait=happy>And truth be told, it's all I need, so I see no point in hoarding more.

Text.SourceString: I’ll get a new one when this one has holes in it.
Text.LocalizedString: I’ll get a new one when this one has holes in it.

Text.SourceString: I like spending my free time here.//<portrait=happy>These animals are my friends.
Text.LocalizedString: I like spending my free time here.//<portrait=happy>These animals are my friends.

Text.SourceString: Why don't we take a little break and chill for a bit?//I’ll put something on the TV if you want.
Text.LocalizedString: Why don't we take a little break and chill for a bit?//I’ll put something on the TV if you want.
